    "causal_summary": "With `EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=auto` (the committed MCP-config default, documented as a local-first cascade `ollama → hf-local → openai → voyage`), the mk-spec-memory daemon silently resolves to **`hf-local`** — which is unhealthy on this host (no running backend) — instead of the active, working **`ollama`** embedder. ollama is up, has `nomic-embed-text:v1.5`, and owns the active vector shard `context-vectors__ollama__nomic-embed-text-v1.5__768`. The result: embeds fail, the retry queue flaps, and `auto` does not deliver the ollama-first behavior it advertises. The current interim mitigation is an explicit `EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=ollama` pin (phase-separate), which is non-portable.",
